documentation.text:
@dev Allows a user to claim their air drop rewards.
 Sends 10% of user's current balance + more depending how long they have been holding their CHES.

natspec.details: Contract responsible for the Chain Estate air drop mechanism

changeAirDropInitialPercent(uint256).details: Only owner function to change the initial percentage gained from air drop rewards before invest time calculation.

params.amount: the new air drop initial percent reward (percent of user's current holdings).

changeAirDropMinimumToInvest(uint256).details: Only owner function to change the minimum amount of CHES a user needs to have to participate in air drops.

params.newMinimum: the new minimum amount of CHES

changeMinimumInvestTime(uint256,bool).details: Only owner function to change how long users need to hold their CHES tokens before being able to claim airdrop rewards.

params.convertToDays: boolean to determine if the number provided should be treated as a number of days (true) or seconds (false).
params.newMinimumTime: the new minimum amount of time users need to have held their CHES tokens for.

claimAirDrop().details: Allows a user to claim their air drop rewards. Sends 10% of user's current balance + more depending how long they have been holding their CHES.

closeAirDrop().details: Only owner function to close the current airdrop. Airdrops by default are never closed, this is just here in case it's needed at some point.

getUserBalance().details: Gets the amount of CHES the sender owns.

returns._0: the CHES balance of the sender

openAirDrop().details: Only owner function to open the air drop so users can claim their rewards.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setToken(address).details: Once the CHES token contract is deployed, this function is used to set a reference to that token in this contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
